offsetting age-related vision loss.

80
00:03:11,780 --> 00:03:15,100
What they discovered is
that just brief exposures

81
00:03:15,100 --> 00:03:17,000
to red light early in the day

82
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:18,960
can offset much of the vision loss

83
00:03:18,960 --> 00:03:21,890
that occurs in people 40 years or older.

84
00:03:21,890 --> 00:03:23,810
And what's remarkable about these studies

85
00:03:23,810 --> 00:03:26,590
is that the entire duration of the therapy

86
00:03:26,590 --> 00:03:28,010
is just one to three minutes,

87
00:03:28,010 --> 00:03:30,130
done just a few times per week.

88
00:03:30,130 --> 00:03:31,400
What's even more exciting

89
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:33,010
is that they understand the mechanism

90
00:03:33,010 --> 00:03:35,000
by which this occurred.

91
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:36,300
The cells in the back of the eye

92
00:03:36,300 --> 00:03:39,230
