1800
01:13:35,340 --> 01:13:36,730
It's fine to get that light

1801
01:13:36,730 --> 01:13:38,860
arriving on your eyes indirectly.

1802
01:13:38,860 --> 01:13:41,380
It's fine to wear eyeglasses
or contact lenses.

1803
01:13:41,380 --> 01:13:43,640
In fact, if you think about
the biology of the eye

1804
01:13:43,640 --> 01:13:45,130
and the way that those lenses work,

1805
01:13:45,130 --> 01:13:47,520
that you will just serve
to focus that light

1806
01:13:47,520 --> 01:13:50,296
onto the very cells that
you want those light beams

1807
01:13:50,296 --> 01:13:51,950
to be delivered to,

1808
01:13:51,950 --> 01:13:54,220
whereas sunglasses that
are highly reflective

1809
01:13:54,220 --> 01:13:56,050
or trying to get your sunlight exposure

1810
01:13:56,050 --> 01:13:58,010
through a windshield of a car

1811
01:13:58,010 --> 01:14:00,980
or through a window simply won't work.

1812
01:14:00,980 --> 01:14:02,100
I'm sorry to tell you,

1813
01:14:02,100 --> 01:14:06,250
but most windows are designed
to filter out the UVB light.

1814
01:14:06,250 --> 01:14:09,050
And if you're somebody who's
really keen on blue blockers

1815
01:14:09,050 --> 01:14:11,040
and you're wearing your
blue blockers all day,

1816
01:14:11,040 --> 01:14:13,060
well, don't wear them outside.

1817
01:14:13,060 --> 01:14:15,950
And in fact, you're probably
doing yourself a disservice

1818
01:14:15,950 --> 01:14:18,310
by wearing them in the
morning and in the daytime.

1819
01:14:18,310 --> 01:14:20,140
There certainly is a
place for blue blockers

1820
01:14:20,140 --> 01:14:21,350
in the evening and nighttime,

1821
01:14:21,350 --> 01:14:24,170
if you're having issues with
falling and staying asleep.

1822
01:14:24,170 --> 01:14:26,070
But if you think about it, blue blockers,

1823
01:14:26,070 --> 01:14:26,903
what they're really doing

1824
01:14:26,903 --> 01:14:30,920
is blocking those short wavelength,
UVB wavelengths of light

1825
01:14:30,920 --> 01:14:33,860
that you so desperately need
to arrive at your retina

1826
01:14:33,860 --> 01:14:35,990
and of course, also onto your skin

1827
01:14:35,990 --> 01:14:38,660
in order to get these
powerful biological effects

1828
01:14:38,660 --> 01:14:40,733
on hormones and on pain reduction.

1829
01:14:42,090 --> 01:14:44,370
And in terms of skin exposure,

1830
01:14:44,370 --> 01:14:46,590
these data also might make
you think a little bit

1831
01:14:46,590 --> 01:14:48,160
about whether or not you
should wear short sleeves

1832
01:14:48,160 --> 01:14:48,993
or long sleeves,

1833
01:14:48,993 --> 01:14:51,830
whether or not you want to wear
shorts or a skirt or pants.

1834
01:14:51,830 --> 01:14:53,960
It's all going to depend
on the context of your life

1835
01:14:53,960 --> 01:14:56,320
and the social and other variables

1836
01:14:56,320 --> 01:14:57,850
that are important, of course.

1837
01:14:57,850 --> 01:15:00,590
I don't know each and every
one of your circumstances,

1838
01:15:00,590 --> 01:15:05,480
so I can't tell you to do
X or Y or Z, nor would I,

1839
01:15:05,480 --> 01:15:07,220
but you might take into consideration

1840
01:15:07,220 --> 01:15:10,330
that it is the total
amount of skin exposure

1841
01:15:10,330 --> 01:15:14,210
that is going to allow you to
capture more or fewer photons,

1842
01:15:14,210 --> 01:15:16,230
depending on, for instance,

1843
01:15:16,230 --> 01:15:18,030
if you're completely cloaked in clothing

1844
01:15:18,030 --> 01:15:21,460
and you're just exposed in
the hands, neck, and face

1845
01:15:21,460 --> 01:15:22,640
such as I am now,

1846
01:15:22,640 --> 01:15:25,150
or whether or not you're
outside in shorts and a T-shirt,

1847
01:15:25,150 --> 01:15:28,360
you're going to get very,
very different patterns

1848
01:15:28,360 --> 01:15:30,840
of biological signaling activation

1849
01:15:30,840 --> 01:15:32,190
in those two circumstances.

1850
01:15:32,190 --> 01:15:33,930
Many of you I'm guessing are wondering

1851
01:15:33,930 --> 01:15:37,170
whether or not you should
seek out UVB exposure

1852
01:15:37,170 --> 01:15:39,660
throughout the entire year
or only in the summer months.

1853
01:15:39,660 --> 01:15:41,680
And that's sort of going to depend

1854
01:15:41,680 --> 01:15:45,260
on whether or not you
experience depression

1855
01:15:45,260 --> 01:15:46,530
in the winter months,

1856
01:15:46,530 --> 01:15:48,920
so called seasonal effective disorder.

1857
01:15:48,920 --> 01:15:51,190
Some people have mild, some
people have severe forms

1858
01:15:51,190 --> 01:15:52,310
of seasonal effective disorder.

1859
01:15:52,310 --> 01:15:55,190
Some people love the fall and
winter and the shorter days.

1860
01:15:55,190 --> 01:15:56,920
They love bundling up.
They love the leaves.

1861
01:15:56,920 --> 01:15:58,210
They love the snow, they love the cold,

1862
01:15:58,210 --> 01:16:00,170
and they don't experience
those psychological lows.

1863
01:16:00,170 --> 01:16:01,960
So it varies tremendously.

1864
01:16:01,960 --> 01:16:03,840
And there are genetic differences

1865
01:16:03,840 --> 01:16:07,830
and birthplace origin differences
that relate to all this,

1866
01:16:07,830 --> 01:16:11,453
but really it has to be considered
on a case-by-case basis.

1867
01:16:12,680 --> 01:16:15,840
I personally believe,
and this was reinforced

1868
01:16:15,840 --> 01:16:19,080
by the director of the chronobiology unit

1869
01:16:19,080 --> 01:16:21,620
at the National Institutes of
Mental Health, Samer Hattar,

1870
01:16:21,620 --> 01:16:25,120
that we would all do well
to get more UVB exposure

1871
01:16:25,120 --> 01:16:27,770
from sunlight throughout the entire year,

1872
01:16:27,770 --> 01:16:29,260
provided we aren't burning our skin

1873
01:16:29,260 --> 01:16:31,423
or damaging our eyes in some way.

1874
01:16:32,470 --> 01:16:34,800
In addition to that,
during the winter months,

1875
01:16:34,800 --> 01:16:38,060
if you do experience some drop in energy

1876
01:16:38,060 --> 01:16:43,030
or increase in depression
or psychological lows,

1877
01:16:43,030 --> 01:16:47,500
it can be very beneficial
to access a SAD lamp.

1878
01:16:47,500 --> 01:16:49,350
Or if you don't want to buy a SAD lamp,

1879
01:16:49,350 --> 01:16:51,270
'cause oftentimes they
can be very expensive,

1880
01:16:51,270 --> 01:16:55,120
you might do well to simply
get a LED lighting panel.

1881
01:16:55,120 --> 01:16:56,490
I've described one before.

1882
01:16:56,490 --> 01:17:00,170
And I want to emphasize that I
have no affiliation whatsoever

1883
01:17:00,170 --> 01:17:01,870
to these commercial sources,

1884
