01:23:21,500 --> 01:23:25,130
and therefore there's less
infection floating around.

2034
01:23:25,130 --> 01:23:27,670
So we are still confronted
with a lot of infections.

2035
01:23:27,670 --> 01:23:29,960
We're just able to combat them better.

2036
01:23:29,960 --> 01:23:31,410
What does this mean in terms of a tool?

2037
01:23:31,410 --> 01:23:33,880
What it means is that
during the winter months,

2038
01:23:33,880 --> 01:23:38,610
we should be especially
conscious of accessing UVB light

2039
01:23:38,610 --> 01:23:41,350
to enhance our spleen function,

2040
01:23:41,350 --> 01:23:43,750
to make sure that our
sympathetic nervous system

2041
01:23:43,750 --> 01:23:46,210
is activated to a sufficient level

2042
01:23:46,210 --> 01:23:49,550
to keep our immune system
deploying all those killer T cells

2043
01:23:49,550 --> 01:23:51,130
and B cells and cytokines

2044
01:23:51,130 --> 01:23:52,890
so that when we encounter the infections,

2045
01:23:52,890 --> 01:23:54,800
as we inevitably will, right,

2046
01:23:54,800 --> 01:23:57,780
we're constantly being bombarded
with potential infections,

2047
01:23:57,780 --> 01:24:00,280
that we can combat those infections well.

2048
01:24:00,280 --> 01:24:02,020
And as just a brief aside,

2049
01:24:02,020 --> 01:24:03,650
but I should mention, a brief aside

2050
01:24:03,650 --> 01:24:07,290
that's related to tens of
thousands of quality studies,

2051
01:24:07,290 --> 01:24:10,580
it is well known that
wound healing is faster

2052
01:24:10,580 --> 01:24:13,940
when we are getting
sufficient UVB exposure.

2053
01:24:13,940 --> 01:24:16,360
Typically, that's associated
with the longer days

2054
01:24:16,360 --> 01:24:17,740
of spring and summer.

2055
01:24:17,740 --> 01:24:21,430
It is known that turnover of hair cells,

2056
01:24:21,430 --> 01:24:23,610
the very cells that
give rise to hair cells

2057
01:24:23,610 --> 01:24:24,443
are called stem cells.

2058
01:24:24,443 --> 01:24:27,080
They live in little
so-called niches in our skin

2059
01:24:27,080 --> 01:24:28,510
with these hair stem cells,

2060
01:24:28,510 --> 01:24:31,040
and your hair grows faster in longer days.

2061
01:24:31,040 --> 01:24:34,490
That too is triggered by UVB exposure,

2062
01:24:34,490 --> 01:24:37,560
not just to the skin, but to the eyes.

2063
01:24:37,560 --> 01:24:38,480
That's right.

2064
01:24:38,480 --> 01:24:39,670
There was a study published

2065
01:24:39,670 --> 01:24:42,310
in the Proceedings of the
National Academy of Sciences

2066
01:24:42,310 --> 01:24:46,260
a couple of years ago that
showed that the exposure

2067
01:24:46,260 --> 01:24:48,590
of those melanopsin
ganglion cells in your eyes

2068
01:24:48,590 --> 01:24:52,230
is absolutely critical for
triggering the turnover

2069
01:24:52,230 --> 01:24:56,380
of stem cells in both the skin and hair,

2070
01:24:56,380 --> 01:24:58,690
and also turns out in nails.

2071
01:24:58,690 --> 01:25:00,810
So if you've noticed that your skin,

2072
01:25:00,810 --> 01:25:03,630
your hair and your nails look
better and turn over more,

2073
01:25:03,630 --> 01:25:06,610
meaning grow faster in longer days,

2074
01:25:06,610 --> 01:25:08,100
that is not on a coincidence.

2075
01:25:08,100 --> 01:25:09,830
That is not just your perception.

2076
01:25:09,830 --> 01:25:13,550
In fact, hair grows more,
skin turns over more,

2077
01:25:13,550 --> 01:25:14,920
meaning it's going to look more youthful.

2078
01:25:14,920 --> 01:25:18,007
You're going to essentially
remove older skin cells

2079
01:25:18,007 --> 01:25:20,360
and replace them with new cells,

2080
01:25:20,360 --> 01:25:23,700
and all the renewing cells
and tissues of our body

2081
01:25:23,700 --> 01:25:24,820
are going to proliferate,

2082
01:25:24,820 --> 01:25:27,450
are going to recreate themselves more

2083
01:25:27,450 --> 01:25:30,290
when we're getting sufficient
UVB light to our eyes

2084
01:25:30,290 --> 01:25:32,010
and also to our skin.

2085
01:25:32,010 --> 01:25:36,230
And so while some of you
may think of light therapies

2086
01:25:36,230 --> 01:25:38,600
such as red light
therapies or UVB therapies

2087
01:25:38,600 --> 01:25:41,050
as kind of new agey, or just biohacking,

2088
01:25:41,050 --> 01:25:42,950
again, a phrase I don't particularly like,

2089
01:25:42,950 --> 01:25:44,250
this notion of biohacking,

2090
01:25:44,250 --> 01:25:47,470
'cause it implies using
one thing for a purpose

2091
01:25:47,470 --> 01:25:49,743
that it was never tended to have,

2092
01:25:50,700 --> 01:25:54,300
well, it turns out that
UVB exposure and red light,

2093
01:25:54,300 --> 01:25:57,550
as we'll soon see, is a very potent form

2094
01:25:57,550 --> 01:26:00,190
of increasing things like
wound healing and skin health

2095
01:26:00,190 --> 01:26:04,710
for very logical
mechanistically backed reasons.

2096
01:26:04,710 --> 01:26:07,520
So while I can't account for everything

2097
01:26:07,520 --> 01:26:08,670
that's being promoted out there

2098
01:26:08,670 --> 01:26:09,900
in terms of this light source

2099
01:26:09,900 --> 01:26:11,310
will help your skin look more youthful

2100
01:26:11,310 --> 01:26:13,463
or will help heal your scars,

2101
01:26:14,400 --> 01:26:17,610
the mechanistic basis for
light having those effects

2102
01:26:17,610 --> 01:26:19,190
makes total sense.

2103
01:26:19,190 --> 01:26:21,290
But what you should consider, however,

2104
01:26:21,290 --> 01:26:23,750
is that if the particular light therapy

2105
01:26:23,750 --> 01:26:27,620
that you're considering
involves very local application

2106
01:26:27,620 --> 01:26:32,610
rather than illuminating
broad swaths of skin,

2107
01:26:32,610 --> 01:26:35,050
and if it has no
involvement with the eyes,

2108
01:26:35,050 --> 01:26:38,900
meaning there's no delivery
of UVB or red light

2109
01:26:38,900 --> 01:26:41,440
or the other light therapy to the eyes,

2110
01:26:41,440 --> 01:26:44,980
it's probably not going to
be as potent a treatment

2111
01:26:44,980 --> 01:26:48,160
as would a more systemic activation

2112
01:26:48,160 --> 01:26:51,130
of larger areas of skin and the eyes.

2113
01:26:51,130 --> 01:26:52,850
Now, again, a cautionary note,

2114
01:26:52,850 --> 01:26:55,090
I don't want people taking
technologies that were designed

2115
01:26:55,090 --> 01:26:58,300
for local application and
beaming those into the eyes.

2116
01:26:58,300 --> 01:26:59,500
That could be very, very bad

2117
01:26:59,500 --> 01:27:02,550
and damaging to your
retinal and other tissues.

2118
01:27:02,550 --> 01:27:05,220
Certainly, wouldn't want
you taking bright light

2119
01:27:05,220 --> 01:27:07,480
of very high intensity of any kind

2120
01:27:07,480 --> 01:27:09,600
and getting cavalier about that.

2121
01:27:09,600 --> 01:27:12,970
Typically, the local
illumination of say a wound

2122
01:27:12,970 --> 01:27:14,410
or a particular patch of acne

2123
01:27:14,410 --> 01:27:17,050
or some other form of skin treatment

2124
01:27:17,050 --> 01:27:18,870
involves very high intensity light.

2125
01:27:18,870 --> 01:27:20,470
And if the intensity is too high,

2126
01:27:20,470 --> 01:27:22,410
you can actually damage that skin.

2127
01:27:22,410 --> 01:27:24,910
And so as we'll talk
about in a few moments,

2128
01:27:24,910 --> 01:27:27,410
most of those therapies for modifying skin

2129
01:27:27,410 --> 01:27:31,640
involve actually burning
off a small, very thin layer

2130
01:27:31,640 --> 01:27:33,510
at the top of the epidermis

2131
01:27:33,510 --> 01:27:35,670
in efforts to trigger the renewal

2132
01:27:35,670 --> 01:27:37,050
or the activation of stem cells

2133
01:27:37,050 --> 01:27:39,890
that will replenish that with new cells.

2134
01:27:39,890 --> 01:27:44,370
So there's a fine line to be
had between light therapies

2135
01:27:44,370 --> 01:27:46,010
that are very localized and intense,

2136
01:27:46,010 --> 01:27:48,190
which are designed to damage skin

2137
01:27:48,190 --> 01:27:52,540
and cause reactivation of new stem cells,

2138
01:27:52,540 --> 01:27:54,780
whether that's hair cells
or skin cells, et cetera,

2139
01:27:54,780 --> 01:27:57,597
versus systemic activation
across broad swaths of skin

2140
01:27:57,597 --> 01:27:58,430
and the eyes.

2141
01:27:58,430 --> 01:28:00,910
You really have to consider
this on a case-by-case basis,

2142
01:28:00,910 --> 01:28:03,740
but at least for now just consider

2143
01:28:03,740 --> 01:28:08,240
that increases in
hormones, reduction in pain

2144
01:28:08,240 --> 01:28:10,680
by way of increases in enkephalin

2145
01:28:10,680 --> 01:28:12,720
and other endogenous opioids,

2146
01:28:12,720 --> 01:28:15,720
improving immune status
by activating the spleen,

2147
01:28:15,720 --> 01:28:17,410
and so on, and so on

2148
01:28:17,410 --> 01:28:19,580
really are all the downstream consequence

2149
01:28:19,580 --> 01:28:21,950
of illuminating large swaths of skin

2150
01:28:21,950 --> 01:28:23,980
and making sure that those
neurons within the eye

2151
01:28:23,980 --> 01:28:26,280
get their adequate UVB exposure

2152
01:28:26,280 --> 01:28:28,270
or other light wavelength exposure,

2153
01:28:28,270 --> 01:28:31,380
not simply beaming a
particular wavelength of light

2154
01:28:31,380 --> 01:28:33,010
at a particular location on the body

2155
01:28:33,010 --> 01:28:35,410
and hoping that that
particular illumination

2156
01:28:35,410 --> 01:28:37,150
at a particular location on the body

2157
01:28:37,150 --> 01:28:40,500
is going to somehow change
the biology at that location.

2158
01:28:40,500 --> 01:28:43,350
Our biology just really
doesn't work that way.

2159
01:28:43,350 --> 01:28:45,270
It's possible, but in general,

2160
01:28:45,270 --> 01:28:48,450
systemic effects through
broad scale illumination

2161
01:28:48,450 --> 01:28:49,730
and illumination to the eye,

2162
01:28:49,730 --> 01:28:52,320
combined with local
treatments are very likely

2163
01:28:52,320 --> 01:28:54,400
to be the ones that have the most success.

2164
01:28:54,400 --> 01:28:55,730
Now, I'd like to shift our attention

2165
01:28:55,730 --> 01:28:58,030
to the effects of light
on mood more specifically.

2166
01:28:58,030 --> 01:28:58,863
We talked about this

2167
01:28:58,863 --> 01:29:00,720
in terms of seasonal effective disorder,

2168
01:29:00,720 --> 01:29:01,890
but many of us don't suffer

2169
01:29:01,890 --> 01:29:03,410
from seasonal effective disorder.

2170
01:29:03,410 --> 01:29:04,880
So I'd like to drill a little deeper

2171
01:29:04,880 --> 01:29:07,670
into how light impacts mood.

2172
01:29:07,670 --> 01:29:11,790
And here, I want to, again,
paraphrase the statements

2173
01:29:11,790 --> 01:29:14,500
of Dr. Samer Hattar

2174
01:29:14,500 --> 01:29:16,810
at the National Institutes
of Mental Health,

2175
01:29:16,810 --> 01:29:18,960
I should mention the director
of the chronobiology unit

2176
01:29:18,960 --> 01:29:20,700
at the National Institutes
of Mental Health

2177
01:29:20,700 --> 01:29:25,700
and perhaps one of the top one
to two to three world experts

2178
01:29:26,040 --> 01:29:28,230
in how light can impact mood, appetite,

2179
01:29:28,230 --> 01:29:29,830
circadian rhythms, and so forth.

2180
01:29:31,690 --> 01:29:33,070
Samer stated on the podcast,

2181
01:29:33,070 --> 01:29:36,240
and he said in various
other venues as well,

2182
01:29:36,240 --> 01:29:40,600
that getting as much UVB light
in our eyes and on our skin

2183
01:29:40,600 --> 01:29:42,410
in the early day and throughout the day

2184
01:29:42,410 --> 01:29:45,530
as is safely possible is going
to be beneficial for mood.

2185
01:29:45,530 --> 01:29:48,140
There's also another time of day,

2186
01:29:48,140 --> 01:29:49,850
or rather I should say a time of night

2187
01:29:49,850 --> 01:29:54,450
in which UVB can be leveraged
in order to improve mood,

2188
01:29:54,450 --> 01:29:56,370
but it's actually the
inverse of everything

2189
01:29:56,370 --> 01:29:58,293
we've been talking about up until now.

2190
01:29:59,410 --> 01:30:02,520
We have a particular neural
circuit that originates

2191
01:30:02,520 --> 01:30:04,940
with those melanopsin cells in our eye

2192
01:30:04,940 --> 01:30:07,250
that bypass all the areas of the brain

2193
01:30:07,250 --> 01:30:09,150
associated with circadian clocks,

2194
01:30:09,150 --> 01:30:11,590
so everything related to
sleep and wakefulness,

2195
01:30:11,590 --> 01:30:14,800
that's specifically
dedicated to the pathways

2196
01:30:14,800 --> 01:30:17,010
involving the release of
molecules like dopamine,

2197
01:30:17,010 --> 01:30:19,940
the neuromodulator that's
associated with motivation,

2198
01:30:19,940 --> 01:30:23,870
with feeling good, with feeling
like there's possibility

2199
01:30:23,870 --> 01:30:25,800
in the world, and so on and so forth,

2200
01:30:25,800 --> 01:30:26,960
and other molecules as well,

2201
01:30:26,960 --> 01:30:29,750
including serotonin and some
of those endogenous opioids

2202
01:30:29,750 --> 01:30:31,150
that we talked about before.

2203
01:30:32,270 --> 01:30:34,390
That particular pathway
involves a brain structure

2204
01:30:34,390 --> 01:30:36,750
called the perihabenular nucleus.

2205
01:30:36,750 --> 01:30:39,740
The perihabenular nucleus gets input

2206
01:30:39,740 --> 01:30:43,440
from the cells in the eye
that respond to UVB light,

2207
01:30:43,440 --> 01:30:46,790
and frankly, to bright light
of other wavelengths as well,

2208
01:30:46,790 --> 01:30:49,490
'cause as you recall, if
a light is bright enough,

2209
01:30:49,490 --> 01:30:51,360
even if it's not UV or blue light,

2210
01:30:51,360 --> 01:30:53,870
it can activate those cells in the eye.

2211
01:30:53,870 --> 01:30:54,770
Those cells in the eye

2212
01:30:54,770 --> 01:30:57,410
communicate to the perihabenular nucleus.

2213
01:30:57,410 --> 01:31:01,110
And as it turns out, if
this pathway is activated

2214
01:31:01,110 --> 01:31:04,780
at the wrong time of each 24-hour cycle,

2215
01:31:04,780 --> 01:31:09,780
mood gets worse, dopamine
output gets worse,

2216
01:31:09,780 --> 01:31:13,210
molecules that are there
specifically to make us feel good,

2217
01:31:13,210 --> 01:31:16,103
actually are reduced in their output.

2218
01:31:17,040 --> 01:31:20,460
So while UVB exposure in the
morning and throughout the day

2219
01:31:21,400 --> 01:31:24,410
is going to be very
important for elevating

2220
01:31:24,410 --> 01:31:26,530
and maintaining elevated mood,

2221
01:31:26,530 --> 01:31:30,870
avoiding UVB light at
night is actually a way

2222
01:31:30,870 --> 01:31:33,700
in which we can prevent activation

2223
01:31:33,700 --> 01:31:36,920
of this eye to perihabenular pathway

2224
01:31:36,920 --> 01:31:38,930
that can actually turn on depression.

2225
01:31:38,930 --> 01:31:41,680
To be very direct and succinct about this,

2226
01:31:41,680 --> 01:31:45,000
avoid exposure to UVB light
from artificial sources

2227
01:31:45,850 --> 01:31:48,480
between the hours of 10:00 pm and 4:00 am.

2228
01:31:48,480 --> 01:31:51,820
And if you're somebody
who suffers from low mood

2229
01:31:51,820 --> 01:31:54,710
and overall has a kind of mild depression

2230
01:31:54,710 --> 01:31:55,980
or even severe depression,

2231
01:31:55,980 --> 01:31:57,930
of course, please see a psychiatrist,

2232
01:31:57,930 --> 01:32:00,970
see a trained psychologist,
get that treated,

2233
01:32:00,970 --> 01:32:05,970
but you would do especially
well to avoid UVB exposure

2234
01:32:06,510 --> 01:32:09,610
from artificial sources, not
just from 10:00 pm to 4:00 am,

2235
01:32:09,610 --> 01:32:13,000
but really be careful about
getting too much exposure to UVB

2236
01:32:13,000 --> 01:32:14,410
even in the late evening,

2237
01:32:14,410 --> 01:32:17,220
so 8:00 pm perhaps to 4:00 am.

2238
01:32:17,220 --> 01:32:19,570
I can't emphasize this enough,

2239
01:32:19,570 --> 01:32:21,790
that if you view UVB light,

2240
01:32:21,790 --> 01:32:24,570
you activate those neurons
in your eye very potently.

2241
01:32:24,570 --> 01:32:28,100
And if those cells communicate
to the perihabenular nucleus,

2242
01:32:28,100 --> 01:32:28,933
which they do,

2243
01:32:28,933 --> 01:32:31,650
you will truncate or reduce
the amount of dopamine

2244
01:32:31,650 --> 01:32:32,500
that you release.

2245
01:32:33,410 --> 01:32:36,160
So if you want to keep your mood elevated,

2246
01:32:36,160 --> 01:32:38,920
get a lot of light, UVB
light, throughout the day,

2247
01:32:38,920 --> 01:32:42,870
and at night, really be cautious
about getting UVB exposure

2248
01:32:42,870 --> 01:32:44,160
from artificial sources.

2249
01:32:44,160 --> 01:32:46,960
Now let's say you're somebody
who has no issues with mood.

2250
01:32:46,960 --> 01:32:49,540
You're just the happiest
person all year long,

2251
01:32:49,540 --> 01:32:52,560
or maybe you just have subtle
variations in your mood.

2252
01:32:52,560 --> 01:32:53,860
You feel great about that.

2253
01:32:55,030 --> 01:32:57,940
Turns out that you still
want to be very careful

2254
01:32:57,940 --> 01:32:59,570
about light exposure

2255
01:32:59,570 --> 01:33:02,870
between the hours of 10:00
pm or so, and 4:00 am,

2256
01:33:02,870 --> 01:33:05,030
in fact, even during sleep.

2257
01:33:05,030 --> 01:33:06,840
There's a recent study that just came out

2258
01:33:06,840 --> 01:33:09,750
in the Proceedings of the
National Academy of Sciences,

2259
01:33:09,750 --> 01:33:12,760
and it's entitled Light
Exposure During Sleep

2260
01:33:12,760 --> 01:33:15,840
Impairs Cardiometabolic Function.

2261
01:33:15,840 --> 01:33:17,690
This is a very interesting study

2262
01:33:17,690 --> 01:33:20,220
where they took human
subjects, young adults,

2263
01:33:20,220 --> 01:33:22,650
and having them sleep in rooms

2264
01:33:22,650 --> 01:33:24,040
that had different lighting conditions,

2265
01:33:24,040 --> 01:33:27,920
either dim light or slightly bright light.

2266
01:33:27,920 --> 01:33:30,490
Now, many people can't fall
asleep in brightly lit rooms,

2267
01:33:30,490 --> 01:33:31,978
so they acknowledge this.

2268
01:33:31,978 --> 01:33:33,960
These were not very brightly lit rooms.

2269
01:33:33,960 --> 01:33:36,260
These were rooms that
had just a little bit

2270
01:33:36,260 --> 01:33:39,260
of overhead room lighting, a hundred lux,

2271
01:33:39,260 --> 01:33:41,290
which is not very bright at all.

2272
01:33:41,290 --> 01:33:43,920
Or they had them sleep in a
room that had very dim light,

2273
01:33:43,920 --> 01:33:45,800
which is less than three lux.

2274
