01:34:03,290 --> 01:34:05,620
and it'll give you an
approximate readout of lux,

2284
01:34:05,620 --> 01:34:07,720
which is the light intensity

2285
01:34:07,720 --> 01:34:10,170
that the phone happens
to be staring out at

2286
01:34:10,170 --> 01:34:11,003
at that location.

2287
01:34:11,003 --> 01:34:14,080
It's not exact, but it's a pretty good

2288
01:34:14,080 --> 01:34:17,460
back-of-the-envelope
measure of light intensity.

2289
01:34:17,460 --> 01:34:20,410
So these subjects were either
sleeping in a very dim room,

2290
01:34:20,410 --> 01:34:22,180
three lux is very, very dim,

2291
01:34:22,180 --> 01:34:25,930
or a somewhat dim room, a hundred lux.

2292
01:34:25,930 --> 01:34:29,210
In this study, they measured
things like melatonin levels.

2293
01:34:29,210 --> 01:34:30,960
They looked at heart rate,

2294
01:34:30,960 --> 01:34:35,940
they looked at measures of
insulin and glucose management.

2295
01:34:35,940 --> 01:34:38,070
Now, in previous episodes,

2296
01:34:38,070 --> 01:34:40,430
I've talked about how
glucose, blood sugar,

2297
01:34:40,430 --> 01:34:42,430
is regulated by insulin

2298
01:34:42,430 --> 01:34:43,960
because you don't want your glucose levels

2299
01:34:43,960 --> 01:34:47,580
to be too high, hyperglycemia,
or too low, hypoglycemia.

2300
01:34:47,580 --> 01:34:50,400
And the hormone insulin is
involved in sequestering

2301
01:34:50,400 --> 01:34:52,520
and shuttling glucose in the bloodstream.

2302
01:34:52,520 --> 01:34:55,410
Basically, how well you manage
glucose in the bloodstream

2303
01:34:55,410 --> 01:34:58,490
can be indirectly measured
by your insulin levels.

2304
01:34:58,490 --> 01:35:01,490
And it's well known that sleep deprivation

2305
01:35:01,490 --> 01:35:06,490
can disrupt glucose regulation by insulin.

2306
01:35:07,000 --> 01:35:09,400
However, in this study,
subjects were sleeping

2307
01:35:09,400 --> 01:35:10,233
the whole night through.

2308
01:35:10,233 --> 01:35:12,170
It just so happens that some
of the subjects were sleeping

2309
01:35:12,170 --> 01:35:13,937
in this very dimly lit room, three lux,

2310
01:35:13,937 --> 01:35:15,410
and other subjects were sleeping

2311
01:35:15,410 --> 01:35:19,760
in a somewhat dimly lit
room, a hundred lux.

2312
01:35:19,760 --> 01:35:21,730
What's incredible about this study

2313
01:35:21,730 --> 01:35:24,180
is that both rooms were
sufficiently dimmed

2314
01:35:24,180 --> 01:35:27,510
that melatonin levels were
not altered in either case.

2315
01:35:27,510 --> 01:35:28,343
This is really key.

2316
01:35:28,343 --> 01:35:31,500
It's not as if one group
experienced a lot of bright light

2317
01:35:31,500 --> 01:35:33,640
through their eyelids and others did not.

2318
01:35:33,640 --> 01:35:35,570
Melatonin levels were not disrupted.

2319
01:35:35,570 --> 01:35:38,280
And given how potently
light can inhibit melatonin,

2320
01:35:38,280 --> 01:35:39,790
this speaks to the fact

2321
01:35:39,790 --> 01:35:42,520
that this very dim condition of three lux

2322
01:35:42,520 --> 01:35:44,890
and the somewhat dim
condition of a hundred lux

2323
01:35:44,890 --> 01:35:48,070
was not actually perceived by the subjects

2324
01:35:48,070 --> 01:35:50,760
nor was it disrupting
these hormone pathways.

2325
01:35:50,760 --> 01:35:53,290
They also looked at glucose responses.

2326
01:35:53,290 --> 01:35:56,480
They had people essentially
take a fasting glucose test

2327
01:35:56,480 --> 01:35:57,380
in different conditions.

2328
01:35:57,380 --> 01:35:58,950
I won't go into all the details,

2329
01:35:58,950 --> 01:36:00,410
but here's what they found.

2330
01:36:00,410 --> 01:36:04,440
In healthy adults, even
just one night of sleeping

2331
01:36:04,440 --> 01:36:06,920
in a moderately lit environment,

2332
01:36:06,920 --> 01:36:10,930
this hundred lux
environment, caused changes,

2333
01:36:10,930 --> 01:36:12,630
increases in nighttime heart rate,

2334
01:36:12,630 --> 01:36:14,440
which means that the
sympathetic nervous system

2335
01:36:14,440 --> 01:36:16,620
was overly active as compared to people

2336
01:36:16,620 --> 01:36:18,340
that slept in a completely dark

2337
01:36:18,340 --> 01:36:20,900
or in a very, very dimly lit room.

2338
01:36:20,900 --> 01:36:23,490
Decreases in heart rate variability,

2339
01:36:23,490 --> 01:36:25,760
and here I should point out
that heart rate variability

2340
01:36:25,760 --> 01:36:28,710
or HRV is a good thing, we
want heart rate variability.

2341
01:36:28,710 --> 01:36:30,380
So they saw increases in heart rate,

2342
01:36:30,380 --> 01:36:32,480
decreases in heart rate variability,

2343
01:36:32,480 --> 01:36:36,360
and increases in next
morning insulin resistance,

2344
01:36:36,360 --> 01:36:40,790
which is an indication that
glucose management is suffering.

2345
01:36:40,790 --> 01:36:43,330
So this is powerful.

2346
01:36:43,330 --> 01:36:45,860
The results of this study
essentially indicate

2347
01:36:45,860 --> 01:36:49,140
that even just one night of
sleeping the whole night through

2348
01:36:49,140 --> 01:36:52,490
in a dimly lit environment
is disrupting the way

2349
01:36:52,490 --> 01:36:54,970
that our autonomic nervous
system is functioning,

2350
01:36:54,970 --> 01:36:57,550
altering so called autonomic tone,

2351
01:36:57,550 --> 01:37:00,300
making us less relaxed
is probably the best way

2352
01:37:00,300 --> 01:37:01,500
to describe it,

2353
01:37:01,500 --> 01:37:03,130
even though we are asleep,

2354
01:37:03,130 --> 01:37:04,460
disrupting the way

2355
01:37:04,460 --> 01:37:07,570
that our cardiometabolic
function operates,

2356
01:37:07,570 --> 01:37:09,860
such that we have lower
heart rate variability

2357
01:37:09,860 --> 01:37:12,910
and increased insulin resistance.

2358
01:37:12,910 --> 01:37:15,690
This is not a good thing
for any of us to experience.

2359
01:37:15,690 --> 01:37:17,630
So while we've mainly been talking

2360
01:37:17,630 --> 01:37:19,480
about the positive effects of UVB light

2361
01:37:19,480 --> 01:37:21,210
and other forms of light,

2362
01:37:21,210 --> 01:37:22,950
now we have two examples.

2363
01:37:22,950 --> 01:37:25,270
One from the work of Hattar and colleagues

2364
01:37:25,270 --> 01:37:28,800
showing that UVB exposure
via the perihabenula

2365
01:37:28,800 --> 01:37:31,370
can diminish the output of dopamine

2366
01:37:31,370 --> 01:37:33,090
and other molecules that make us feel good

2367
01:37:33,090 --> 01:37:35,380
if that UVB exposure is
in the middle of the night

2368
01:37:35,380 --> 01:37:36,810
or late evening.

2369
01:37:36,810 --> 01:37:39,330
And now we have yet
another study performed,

2370
01:37:39,330 --> 01:37:40,840
in this case, in humans,

2371
01:37:40,840 --> 01:37:42,957
indicating that even if we fall asleep

2372
01:37:42,957 --> 01:37:44,580
and sleep the whole night through,

2373
01:37:44,580 --> 01:37:47,540
if the room that we're
sleeping in has too many lux,

2374
01:37:47,540 --> 01:37:48,860
too much light energy,

2375
01:37:48,860 --> 01:37:51,860
that light energy is no doubt
going through the eyelids,

2376
01:37:51,860 --> 01:37:54,930
which it can, activating
the particular cells

2377
01:37:54,930 --> 01:37:57,930
in the eye that trigger an increase

2378
01:37:57,930 --> 01:37:59,910
in sympathetic nervous system activation

2379
01:37:59,910 --> 01:38:02,370
and disrupting our metabolism.

2380
01:38:02,370 --> 01:38:05,660
And this study rests on a
number of other recent studies

2381
01:38:05,660 --> 01:38:07,960
published in Cell, which
is a superb journal,

2382
01:38:07,960 --> 01:38:10,210
and other journals, showing
that during the course

2383
01:38:10,210 --> 01:38:13,090
of a healthy, deep night's sleep,

2384
01:38:13,090 --> 01:38:14,187
our body actually transitions

2385
01:38:14,187 --> 01:38:16,800
through various forms
of metabolic function.

2386
01:38:16,800 --> 01:38:20,420
We actually experience
ketosis-like states.

2387
01:38:20,420 --> 01:38:23,000
We experience glucogenesis.

2388
01:38:23,000 --> 01:38:25,240
We experience different
forms of metabolism

2389
01:38:25,240 --> 01:38:27,230
associated with different stages of sleep,

2390
01:38:27,230 --> 01:38:29,080
not something that we're
going into in depth

2391
01:38:29,080 --> 01:38:31,800
in this podcast, we will
in a future podcast.

2392
01:38:31,800 --> 01:38:35,970
What this study shows is that
light exposure even in sleep

2393
01:38:35,970 --> 01:38:38,530
is disrupting our autonomic, in this case,

2394
01:38:38,530 --> 01:38:40,950
the sympathetic arm of the
autonomic nervous system

2395
01:38:40,950 --> 01:38:44,280
in ways that are disrupting
metabolism, probably in sleep,

2396
01:38:44,280 --> 01:38:47,030
but certainly outside of
sleep so that we wake up

2397
01:38:47,030 --> 01:38:48,450
and have our first meal of the day.

2398
01:38:48,450 --> 01:38:49,700
Or even if you're intermittent fasting,

2399
01:38:49,700 --> 01:38:51,320
you eat that first meal of the day,

2400
01:38:51,320 --> 01:38:54,310
if your sleep is taking
place in an environment

2401
01:38:54,310 --> 01:38:56,590
that's overly illuminated,

2402
01:38:56,590 --> 01:38:59,310
well, that's disrupting
your cardiac function

2403
01:38:59,310 --> 01:39:00,720
and your metabolism.

2404
01:39:00,720 --> 01:39:02,480
I've been talking a lot about UVB light,

2405
01:39:02,480 --> 01:39:04,150
which is short wavelength light.

2406
01:39:04,150 --> 01:39:05,270
So UV light, blue light,

2407
01:39:05,270 --> 01:39:07,180
maybe even some blue green light,

2408
01:39:07,180 --> 01:39:08,680
that's going to be short wavelength light.

2409
01:39:08,680 --> 01:39:09,800
Now, I'd like to shift our attention

2410
01:39:09,800 --> 01:39:11,160
to the other end of the spectrum,

2411
01:39:11,160 --> 01:39:12,350
meaning the light spectrum,

2412
01:39:12,350 --> 01:39:14,360
to talk about red light
and infrared light,

2413
01:39:14,360 --> 01:39:16,250
which is long wavelength light.

2414
01:39:16,250 --> 01:39:19,970
Many so-called low level light therapies,

2415
01:39:19,970 --> 01:39:23,990
the acronym is LLLT, low
level light therapies,

2416
01:39:23,990 --> 01:39:27,600
involve the use of red
light and infrared light.

2417
01:39:27,600 --> 01:39:31,100
Sometimes, low level light
therapies involve the use of UVB,

2418
01:39:31,100 --> 01:39:32,760
but more often than not these days,

2419
01:39:32,760 --> 01:39:35,760
when we hear LLLT, low
level light therapy,

2420
01:39:35,760 --> 01:39:37,540
it's referring to red light

2421
01:39:37,540 --> 01:39:40,003
and near-infrared light therapies.

2422
01:39:41,950 --> 01:39:44,610
Low level light therapies have
been shown to be effective

2423
01:39:44,610 --> 01:39:47,640
for a huge number of biological phenomenon

2424
01:39:47,640 --> 01:39:49,420
and medical treatments.

2425
01:39:49,420 --> 01:39:50,940
I can't summarize all of those now.

2426
01:39:50,940 --> 01:39:52,770
It would take me many, many hours.

2427
01:39:52,770 --> 01:39:55,410
It would be an effective
episode for curing insomnia,

2428
01:39:55,410 --> 01:39:58,810
but it wouldn't inform you
properly about the use of light

2429
01:39:58,810 --> 01:39:59,800
for your health.

2430
01:39:59,800 --> 01:40:01,380
Rather, I'd like to just emphasize

2431
01:40:01,380 --> 01:40:03,550
some of the top contour of those studies

2432
01:40:03,550 --> 01:40:06,010
and point out that for instance,

2433
01:40:06,010 --> 01:40:08,160
low level light therapy
with infrared light

2434
01:40:08,160 --> 01:40:10,960
has been shown to be effective
for the treatment of acne

2435
01:40:10,960 --> 01:40:13,000
and other sorts of skin lesions.

2436
01:40:13,000 --> 01:40:15,200
There have been some really
nice studies actually

2437
01:40:15,200 --> 01:40:18,010
where they use subjects as
their own internal control.

2438
01:40:18,010 --> 01:40:19,150
So people, believe it or not,

2439
01:40:19,150 --> 01:40:20,820
agreed to have half of their face

2440
01:40:20,820 --> 01:40:23,910
illuminated with red light
or near-infrared light,

2441
01:40:23,910 --> 01:40:26,050
and the other half of their
face serve as a control,

2442
01:40:26,050 --> 01:40:28,330
and to do that for
several weeks at a time.

2443
01:40:28,330 --> 01:40:31,100
And you can see pretty
impressive reductions

2444
01:40:31,100 --> 01:40:35,220
in skin lesions, reductions
in scars from acne,

2445
01:40:35,220 --> 01:40:38,220
and reduction in acne lesions themselves,

2446
01:40:38,220 --> 01:40:41,020
meaning the accumulation of new acne cysts

2447
01:40:41,020 --> 01:40:42,570
with low level light therapy,

2448
01:40:42,570 --> 01:40:44,600
using red light and infrared light.

2449
01:40:44,600 --> 01:40:49,280
Sometimes however, there is
a resistance of that acne

2450
01:40:49,280 --> 01:40:50,620
to the low level light therapy,

2451
01:40:50,620 --> 01:40:52,800
such that people will get
an initial improvement,

2452
01:40:52,800 --> 01:40:55,700
and then it'll go away despite
continuing the treatment.

2453
01:40:55,700 --> 01:40:58,270
So you're probably asking, or
at least you should be asking,

2454
01:40:58,270 --> 01:41:00,770
how is it that shining
red light on our skin

2455
01:41:00,770 --> 01:41:04,640
can impact things like acne
and wound healing, et cetera?

2456
01:41:04,640 --> 01:41:06,760
Well, to understand that,
we have to think back

2457
01:41:06,760 --> 01:41:08,370
to the beginning of the episode

2458
01:41:08,370 --> 01:41:10,730
where I described how
long wavelength light,

2459
01:41:10,730 --> 01:41:13,100
such as red light and near-infrared light,

2460
01:41:13,100 --> 01:41:15,160
which is even longer than red light,

2461
01:41:15,160 --> 01:41:19,180
can pass through certain
surfaces, including our skin.

2462
01:41:19,180 --> 01:41:21,830
So our skin has an epidermis,
which is on the outside,

2463
01:41:21,830 --> 01:41:24,440
and the dermis, which
is in the deeper layers.

2464
01:41:24,440 --> 01:41:27,150
Red light and infrared light can pass down

2465
01:41:27,150 --> 01:41:29,060
into the deeper layers of our skin,

2466
01:41:29,060 --> 01:41:31,437
where it can change the metabolic function

2467
01:41:31,437 --> 01:41:32,900
of particular cells.

2468
01:41:32,900 --> 01:41:35,650
So let's just take acne as an example.

2469
01:41:35,650 --> 01:41:37,930
Within the dermis, the
deep layers of our skin,

2470
01:41:37,930 --> 01:41:39,730
we have what are called sebaceous glands

2471
01:41:39,730 --> 01:41:43,740
that actually make the oil
that is present in our skin.

2472
01:41:43,740 --> 01:41:46,710
Those sebaceous glands are
often nearby hair follicles.

2473
01:41:46,710 --> 01:41:49,313
So if you've ever had a
infected hair follicle,

2474
01:41:50,150 --> 01:41:51,520
that's not a coincidence

2475
01:41:51,520 --> 01:41:53,120
that hair follicles tend to get infected.

2476
01:41:53,120 --> 01:41:56,270
Part of it is because there's
actually a portal down

2477
01:41:56,270 --> 01:41:57,128
and around the hair follicle,

2478
01:41:57,128 --> 01:42:00,550
but the sebaceous gland is
where the oil is created.

2479
01:42:00,550 --> 01:42:03,800
That is going to give rise to,
for instance, acne lesions.

2480
01:42:03,800 --> 01:42:06,940
Also, in the dermis, in the
deep layers of the skin,

2481
01:42:06,940 --> 01:42:08,020
are the melanocytes.

2482
01:42:08,020 --> 01:42:08,960
They're not just in the epidermis,

2483
01:42:08,960 --> 01:42:11,820
they're also in the
deeper layers of the skin.

2484
01:42:11,820 --> 01:42:14,780
And you have the stem cells that give rise

2485
01:42:14,780 --> 01:42:16,860
to additional skin cells.

2486
01:42:16,860 --> 01:42:19,240
If the top layers of the
epidermis are damaged,

2487
01:42:19,240 --> 01:42:21,300
those stem cells can become activated.

2488
01:42:21,300 --> 01:42:23,570
And you also have the stem cells

2489
01:42:23,570 --> 01:42:25,380
that give rise to hair follicles.

2490
01:42:25,380 --> 01:42:29,680
So by shining red light
or near-infrared light

2491
01:42:29,680 --> 01:42:31,630
on a localized patch of skin,

2492
01:42:31,630 --> 01:42:34,980
provided that red light is
not of such high intensity

2493
01:42:34,980 --> 01:42:36,550
that it burns the skin,

2494
01:42:36,550 --> 01:42:39,150
but is of sufficient
intensity that it provides

2495
01:42:39,150 --> 01:42:42,480
just a little bit of damage to
the upper layers of the skin,

2496
01:42:42,480 --> 01:42:43,860
the epidermis,

2497
01:42:43,860 --> 01:42:47,240
and that it triggers
certain biological pathways

2498
01:42:47,240 --> 01:42:49,540
within the cells of the sebaceous gland

2499
01:42:49,540 --> 01:42:52,510
and the stem cells within
the hair cell niche

2500
01:42:52,510 --> 01:42:54,050
and the stem cells in skin,

2501
01:42:54,050 --> 01:42:56,690
what happens is the top layers of the skin

2502
01:42:56,690 --> 01:43:00,510
are basically burned off
by a very low level of burn

2503
01:43:00,510 --> 01:43:02,460
and/or the cells in the deeper layer

2504
01:43:02,460 --> 01:43:03,930
start to churn out new cells,

2505
01:43:03,930 --> 01:43:07,400
which go and rescue the lesion,

2506
01:43:07,400 --> 01:43:10,670
essentially clear out the
lesion and replace that lesion

2507
01:43:10,670 --> 01:43:12,033
with healthy skin cells.

2508
01:43:13,620 --> 01:43:17,470
This does work in the
context of wound healing,

2509
01:43:17,470 --> 01:43:19,050
getting scars to disappear.

2510
01:43:19,050 --> 01:43:23,010
It also works to remove certain
patches of pigmentation.

2511
01:43:23,010 --> 01:43:24,010
There are sometimes cases

2512
01:43:24,010 --> 01:43:26,900
where people will get a red blotchiness

2513
01:43:26,900 --> 01:43:28,610
due to certain skin conditions

2514
01:43:28,610 --> 01:43:31,370
or some darker pigmentation
that they want remove,

2515
01:43:31,370 --> 01:43:32,610
or that they need removed,

2516
01:43:32,610 --> 01:43:36,070
because it's a potential
skin cancer threat.

2517
01:43:36,070 --> 01:43:37,880
Now, how is red light actually doing it

2518
01:43:37,880 --> 01:43:39,550
within the cells of the sebaceous gland,

2519
01:43:39,550 --> 01:43:41,040
the stem cells, et cetera?

2520
01:43:41,040 --> 01:43:43,220
Well, long wavelength light

2521
01:43:43,220 --> 01:43:45,220
can actually get deep into the skin,

2522
01:43:45,220 --> 01:43:46,053
I mentioned that before,

2523
01:43:46,053 --> 01:43:49,800
but can also get into individual cells

2524
01:43:49,800 --> 01:43:51,760
and can access the so-called organelles,

2525
01:43:51,760 --> 01:43:53,380
which I described at the
beginning of the episode.

2526
01:43:53,380 --> 01:43:55,830
In particular, they can
access the mitochondria,

2527
01:43:55,830 --> 01:43:58,560
which are responsible for producing ATP.

2528
01:43:58,560 --> 01:44:00,580
Now, the simple way to think about this

2529
01:44:00,580 --> 01:44:05,580
for sake of this discussion
is that as cells age,

2530
01:44:06,160 --> 01:44:09,143
and in particular, in very
metabolically active cells,

2531
01:44:10,360 --> 01:44:12,830
they accumulate what are called ROSs,

2532
01:44:12,830 --> 01:44:15,010
reactive oxygen species.

2533
01:44:15,010 --> 01:44:18,810
And as reactive oxygen species go up,

2534
01:44:18,810 --> 01:44:22,390
ATP energy production in
