2670
01:49:54,020 --> 01:49:55,240
This is absolutely critical.

2671
01:49:55,240 --> 01:49:59,410
We know that we don't
accumulate many new brain cells

2672
01:49:59,410 --> 01:50:00,243
as we get older.

2673
01:50:00,243 --> 01:50:02,270
And in some areas of our nervous system,

2674
01:50:02,270 --> 01:50:05,330
such as our neural retina,
which is the part of our eye,

2675
01:50:05,330 --> 01:50:07,630
that's responsible for
translating light information

2676
01:50:07,630 --> 01:50:10,200
to electrical signals so that we can see,

2677
01:50:10,200 --> 01:50:12,810
we don't get any new cells after the time

2678
01:50:12,810 --> 01:50:14,020
in which we were born.

2679
01:50:14,020 --> 01:50:16,600
So the ability to keep our neurons healthy

2680
01:50:16,600 --> 01:50:19,430
is extremely important
for our visual system,

2681
01:50:19,430 --> 01:50:22,190
extremely important for our hippocampus,

2682
01:50:22,190 --> 01:50:24,300
an area of the brain involved in memory.

2683
01:50:24,300 --> 01:50:26,610
And I should just mention that even

2684
01:50:26,610 --> 01:50:28,080
if people don't get Alzheimer's,

2685
01:50:28,080 --> 01:50:30,010
there's always going to be some degree

2686
01:50:30,010 --> 01:50:31,900
of age-related dementia.

2687
01:50:31,900 --> 01:50:35,700
Sadly, nobody is as cognitively sharp

2688
01:50:35,700 --> 01:50:36,990
in the years before they die,

2689
01:50:36,990 --> 01:50:39,240
as they are 20 years before that.

2690
01:50:39,240 --> 01:50:40,360
It's just never the case.

2691
01:50:40,360 --> 01:50:42,550
We're all getting worse at thinking,

2692
01:50:42,550 --> 01:50:44,530
feeling, perceiving, et cetera.

2693
01:50:44,530 --> 01:50:46,730
The question is how quickly
we are getting worse.

2694
01:50:46,730 --> 01:50:49,590
So any mechanism by which we can preserve

2695
01:50:49,590 --> 01:50:51,640
or reverse neuronal function

2696
01:50:51,640 --> 01:50:54,393
turns out to be immensely beneficial.

2697
01:50:55,400 --> 01:50:59,020
The Jeffery Lab has published
two studies in recent years

2698
01:50:59,020 --> 01:51:03,540
on humans that looked
directly, no pun intended,

2699
01:51:03,540 --> 01:51:05,830
at how red light and near-infrared light

2700
01:51:05,830 --> 01:51:08,330
can improve visual function.

2701
01:51:08,330 --> 01:51:10,350
I'm going to describe the
parameters of those studies.

2702
01:51:10,350 --> 01:51:13,263
And then I'm going to describe
what they found, exactly.

2703
01:51:14,470 --> 01:51:18,350
The mechanistic motivation
for these studies, again,

2704
01:51:18,350 --> 01:51:22,520
traces back to this effect
of light on mitochondria.

2705
01:51:22,520 --> 01:51:23,500
So to go a little bit deeper

2706
01:51:23,500 --> 01:51:25,920
into that mechanism just briefly

2707
01:51:25,920 --> 01:51:28,170
so that you can frame
any potential protocol

2708
01:51:28,170 --> 01:51:29,453
that you would develop,

2709
01:51:30,640 --> 01:51:35,640
when light arrives on
cells, including neurons,

2710
01:51:36,050 --> 01:51:37,650
that light can penetrate into the cells

2711
01:51:37,650 --> 01:51:39,020
if it's of the appropriate wavelength.

2712
01:51:39,020 --> 01:51:40,820
Red light can do that,
it can get into cells,

2713
01:51:40,820 --> 01:51:42,270
it can access the mitochondria,

2714
01:51:42,270 --> 01:51:44,043
it can increase ATP.

2715
01:51:44,900 --> 01:51:47,870
In general, anytime ATP is doing its thing

2716
01:51:47,870 --> 01:51:50,100
to increase energy in cells,

2717
01:51:50,100 --> 01:51:54,480
it's involving this thing
called cytochrome c,

2718
01:51:54,480 --> 01:51:55,640
which is an oxidase.

2719
01:51:55,640 --> 01:51:58,770
Anytime you hear ase, A-S-E, in biology,

2720
01:51:58,770 --> 01:51:59,830
it's going to be an enzyme.

2721
01:51:59,830 --> 01:52:02,970
It's involved in some process
of degrading a molecule

2722
01:52:02,970 --> 01:52:05,240
and creating another molecule, typically.

2723
01:52:05,240 --> 01:52:08,480
So ATP and cytochrome c
is going to give you ATP.

2724
01:52:08,480 --> 01:52:13,330
Now, that's a great thing,
but it creates a byproduct.

2725
01:52:13,330 --> 01:52:16,120
It breaks things down, such
that you get these ROSs,

2726
01:52:16,120 --> 01:52:18,120
these reactive oxygen species.

2727
01:52:18,120 --> 01:52:19,900
And those reactive oxygen species,

2728
01:52:19,900 --> 01:52:21,190
for those of you that want to know,

2729
01:52:21,190 --> 01:52:23,900
are involved in things
like redox signaling.

2730
01:52:23,900 --> 01:52:27,320
And reactive oxygen
species actually change

2731
01:52:27,320 --> 01:52:29,610
which genes are made in a cell.

2732
01:52:29,610 --> 01:52:32,300
So the goal of any
treatment is to keep neurons

2733
01:52:32,300 --> 01:52:35,880
or other cells youthful
and functioning well,

2734
01:52:35,880 --> 01:52:38,920
and to prevent or reverse aging,

2735
01:52:38,920 --> 01:52:41,350
is going to be to increase ATP

2736
01:52:41,350 --> 01:52:44,180
and to reduce reactive oxygen species,

2737
01:52:44,180 --> 01:52:48,530
and in doing so, to disrupt
some of the normal pathways

2738
01:52:48,530 --> 01:52:50,253
associated with aging.

2739
01:52:51,910 --> 01:52:53,640
The Jeffery Lab approached these studies

2740
01:52:53,640 --> 01:52:55,840
with that understanding
of how mitochondria

2741
01:52:55,840 --> 01:52:58,420
and reactive oxygen species and ATP work.

2742
01:52:58,420 --> 01:53:01,620
And what they did was exquisitely simple

2743
01:53:01,620 --> 01:53:02,910
to the point of being elegant.

2744
01:53:02,910 --> 01:53:05,290
And what they found was
really, really exciting.

2745
01:53:05,290 --> 01:53:08,650
What they did is they had people,

2746
01:53:08,650 --> 01:53:11,450
subjects that were either
younger, so in their 20s,

2747
01:53:11,450 --> 01:53:14,023
or 40 years old or older,

2748
01:53:15,030 --> 01:53:18,010
view red light of about 670 nanometers.

2749
01:53:18,010 --> 01:53:21,540
670 nanometers would
appear red to you and me.

2750
01:53:21,540 --> 01:53:23,660
They, they had them do that, excuse me,

2751
01:53:23,660 --> 01:53:25,660
at a distance that was
safe for their eyes,

2752
01:53:25,660 --> 01:53:27,770
so at about a foot away.

2753
01:53:27,770 --> 01:53:31,730
Now, a foot away from a
very intense red light

2754
01:53:31,730 --> 01:53:33,060
could actually be damaging to the eyes,

2755
01:53:33,060 --> 01:53:35,240
so they had them do this
at about a foot away

2756
01:53:35,240 --> 01:53:37,990
from a red light that was
of low enough intensity

2757
01:53:37,990 --> 01:53:39,990
that it did not damage the eyes.

2758
01:53:39,990 --> 01:53:41,310
And they had them do that anywhere

2759
01:53:41,310 --> 01:53:44,150
from two to three minutes per day.

2760
01:53:44,150 --> 01:53:45,880
And in one study, they had them do that

2761
01:53:45,880 --> 01:53:48,390
for a long period of
time of about 12 weeks.

2762
01:53:48,390 --> 01:53:49,223
And in the other study,

2763
01:53:49,223 --> 01:53:51,720
they had them do that just
for a couple of weeks.

2764
01:53:51,720 --> 01:53:54,600
What's remarkable is that
when you collapse the results

2765
01:53:54,600 --> 01:53:56,130
across these two studies,

2766
01:53:56,130 --> 01:53:58,710
what they found is that when
looking at these subjects

2767
01:53:58,710 --> 01:54:02,920
ranging from 28 years old
to about 72 years old,

2768
01:54:02,920 --> 01:54:06,430
the major findings were
that in individuals

2769
01:54:06,430 --> 01:54:08,960
40 years old or older,

2770
01:54:08,960 --> 01:54:12,970
so in the 40 to 72-year-old bracket,

2771
01:54:12,970 --> 01:54:16,650
but not in the subjects
younger than 40 years old,

2772
01:54:16,650 --> 01:54:20,160
they saw an improvement
in visual function.

2773
01:54:20,160 --> 01:54:21,500
That improvement in visual function

2774
01:54:21,500 --> 01:54:23,820
was an improvement in visual acuity,

2775
01:54:23,820 --> 01:54:26,900
meaning the ability to
resolve fine detail,

2776
01:54:26,900 --> 01:54:30,520
and using a particular
measure of visual function,

2777
01:54:30,520 --> 01:54:34,120
which is called the Tritan exam.

2778
01:54:34,120 --> 01:54:36,940
T-R-I-T-A-N, Tritan exam,

2779
01:54:36,940 --> 01:54:40,370
which specifically addresses the function

2780
01:54:40,370 --> 01:54:42,400
of the so-called short wavelength cones,

2781
01:54:42,400 --> 01:54:45,040
the ones that respond
to green and blue light,

2782
01:54:45,040 --> 01:54:48,880
they saw a 22% improvement
in visual acuity,

2783
01:54:48,880 --> 01:54:52,270
which in the landscape of visual testing

2784
01:54:52,270 --> 01:54:55,400
is an extremely exciting result.

