Okay, so I think in most studies
of improvements of vision,

2786
01:54:59,260 --> 01:55:03,350
you'd be very excited to see
an improvement of 5% or 10%.

2787
01:55:03,350 --> 01:55:06,560
So a 22% improvement in visual acuity,

2788
01:55:06,560 --> 01:55:09,020
even though it's in
this very specific form

2789
01:55:09,020 --> 01:55:12,733
of visual testing, this Tritan
exam or this Tritan score,

2790
01:55:13,760 --> 01:55:16,050
well, that turns out
to be very significant

2791
01:55:16,050 --> 01:55:20,230
and translates to the real
world in an important way.

2792
01:55:20,230 --> 01:55:23,110
In particular, as we age,

2793
01:55:23,110 --> 01:55:26,160
we tend to lose certain
neurons within our retina,

2794
01:55:26,160 --> 01:55:28,550
but we don't tend to lose cones.

2795
01:55:28,550 --> 01:55:30,210
We tend to lose rods.

2796
01:55:30,210 --> 01:55:32,320
We tend to lose other
cells within the retina,

2797
01:55:32,320 --> 01:55:34,290
including the cells that
connect the eye to the brain,

2798
01:55:34,290 --> 01:55:35,840
the so-called ganglion cells.

2799
01:55:35,840 --> 01:55:37,620
Cones, for whatever reason,

2800
01:55:37,620 --> 01:55:40,260
are pretty resilient to age-related loss.

2801
01:55:40,260 --> 01:55:44,510
However, because rods and cones both

2802
01:55:44,510 --> 01:55:47,760
are not just among the most
metabolically active cells

2803
01:55:47,760 --> 01:55:49,150
in your entire body,

2804
01:55:49,150 --> 01:55:53,010
but the most metabolically
active cells in your entire body

2805
01:55:53,010 --> 01:55:56,250
that's right, your rods and
cones are the cells that demand,

2806
01:55:56,250 --> 01:55:59,893
and that use the most energy
of all the cells in your body,

2807
01:56:00,980 --> 01:56:01,860
not your skin cells,

2808
01:56:01,860 --> 01:56:03,760
not your spleen, not your stomach cells.

2809
01:56:03,760 --> 01:56:04,960
Even if you talk a lot,

2810
01:56:04,960 --> 01:56:07,180
not the cells that are
responsible for moving your mouth.

2811
01:56:07,180 --> 01:56:09,720
It is the rods and cones
of your neural retina

2812
01:56:09,720 --> 01:56:13,047
that are responsible for
using the most amount of ATP

2813
01:56:13,047 --> 01:56:15,660
and energy in your entire body.

2814
01:56:15,660 --> 01:56:17,010
And because of that,

2815
01:56:17,010 --> 01:56:19,710
those cells tend to accumulate a lot

2816
01:56:19,710 --> 01:56:22,293
of reactive oxygen species as we age.

2817
01:56:23,180 --> 01:56:25,410
Red light of the sort
used in these studies

2818
01:56:25,410 --> 01:56:29,970
was able to reduce the amount
of reactive oxygen species

2819
01:56:29,970 --> 01:56:33,380
in the rods and cones and
to rescue the function

2820
01:56:33,380 --> 01:56:35,240
of this particular cone type,

2821
01:56:35,240 --> 01:56:37,060
the short wavelength and
medium wavelength cones,

2822
01:56:37,060 --> 01:56:38,500
which if you think about the study,

2823
01:56:38,500 --> 01:56:39,750
is a little bit surprising,

2824
01:56:39,750 --> 01:56:42,380
because it was red light
and near-infrared light,

2825
01:56:42,380 --> 01:56:44,120
not short wavelength light,

2826
01:56:44,120 --> 01:56:47,040
that was used in order to
create this improvement

2827
01:56:47,040 --> 01:56:48,550
in cellular function.

2828
01:56:48,550 --> 01:56:51,010
But if you step back a little bit further,

2829
01:56:51,010 --> 01:56:54,750
it makes perfect sense because
there's nothing specific

2830
01:56:54,750 --> 01:56:56,270
about the red light in the sense

2831
01:56:56,270 --> 01:56:59,590
that it gets delivered only to red cones.

2832
01:56:59,590 --> 01:57:02,410
That red light and near-infrared
light is being absorbed

2833
01:57:02,410 --> 01:57:04,690
by all the photoreceptors within the eye,

2834
01:57:04,690 --> 01:57:06,670
the rods and the blue cones

2835
01:57:06,670 --> 01:57:08,460
and the green cones and the red cones.

2836
01:57:08,460 --> 01:57:11,800
It's just that the red cones
absorb that light best.

2837
01:57:11,800 --> 01:57:14,580
So the important takeaway here

2838
01:57:14,580 --> 01:57:17,880
is that viewing red light
and near-infrared light

2839
01:57:17,880 --> 01:57:19,820
at a distance at which it is safe

2840
01:57:19,820 --> 01:57:22,460
for just a couple of minutes each day

2841
01:57:22,460 --> 01:57:25,940
allowed a reversal of the
aging process of these neurons,

2842
01:57:25,940 --> 01:57:28,660
which some people have
heard me say before,

2843
01:57:28,660 --> 01:57:30,350
and I'll just say it again,

2844
01:57:30,350 --> 01:57:32,230
the retina, including your photoreceptors,

2845
01:57:32,230 --> 01:57:34,210
are not just connected to your brain.

2846
01:57:34,210 --> 01:57:35,310
They're not just near your brain.

2847
01:57:35,310 --> 01:57:37,450
They are actual central
nervous system tissue.

2848
01:57:37,450 --> 01:57:39,590
They are the only two
pieces of your brain,

2849
01:57:39,590 --> 01:57:41,500
meaning your neuroretinas
are the only two pieces

2850
01:57:41,500 --> 01:57:43,330
of your brain that reside
outside your skull,

2851
01:57:43,330 --> 01:57:45,050
or at least outside the cranial vault.

2852
01:57:45,050 --> 01:57:48,300
So here we're seeing a
reversal of the aging process

2853
01:57:48,300 --> 01:57:51,600
in neurons by shining red
light on those neurons.

2854
01:57:51,600 --> 01:57:54,100
Now, of course, the Jeffery Lab

2855
01:57:54,100 --> 01:57:55,750
