2983
02:02:41,650 --> 02:02:44,870
And if you're older than 40,

2984
02:02:44,870 --> 02:02:46,240
that could very well have an effect.

2985
02:02:46,240 --> 02:02:48,560
If you're longer, younger
than 40, excuse me,

2986
02:02:48,560 --> 02:02:50,800
that's unlikely to have an effect.

2987
02:02:50,800 --> 02:02:52,500
At least that was what was observed

2988
02:02:52,500 --> 02:02:54,110
in these particular studies.

2989
02:02:54,110 --> 02:02:55,560
The lights were not flashing.

2990
02:02:55,560 --> 02:02:57,260
It was continuous illumination.

2991
02:02:57,260 --> 02:02:58,840
Again, you're allowed to blink.

2992
02:02:58,840 --> 02:03:00,660
It does not have to even
be direct illumination.

2993
02:03:00,660 --> 02:03:02,500
It can be somewhat indirect illumination,

2994
02:03:02,500 --> 02:03:06,260
much as we described for
the use of UVB light before.

2995
02:03:06,260 --> 02:03:08,230
The wavelength of light is important.

2996
02:03:08,230 --> 02:03:10,220
It is red light and near-infrared light

2997
02:03:10,220 --> 02:03:14,050
that is going to be
effective in this scenario.

2998
02:03:14,050 --> 02:03:16,760
The authors of this study
emphasized that it was red light

2999
02:03:16,760 --> 02:03:20,270
of 670 nanometers in wavelength

3000
02:03:20,270 --> 02:03:25,270
and near-infrared light of
790 nanometers in wavelength

3001
02:03:25,810 --> 02:03:26,870
that were effective

3002
02:03:26,870 --> 02:03:29,760
and that those wavelengths
could be complimentary.

3003
02:03:29,760 --> 02:03:33,240
That's probably why, or
maybe it's just coincidental,

3004
02:03:33,240 --> 02:03:35,270
but it's a fortunate coincidence

3005
02:03:35,270 --> 02:03:37,730
that a lot of the commercially
available red light panels

3006
02:03:37,730 --> 02:03:38,563
that you'll find out there

3007
02:03:38,563 --> 02:03:41,510
combine both red light
and near-infrared light.

3008
02:03:41,510 --> 02:03:44,310
However, I want to emphasize
that most of the panels

3009
02:03:44,310 --> 02:03:46,120
that are commercially available

3010
02:03:46,120 --> 02:03:50,520
are going to be too bright to
safely look at very close up.

3011
02:03:50,520 --> 02:03:53,040
And in fact, that's why most
of those red light panels

3012
02:03:53,040 --> 02:03:55,010
are designed for illumination of the skin

3013
02:03:55,010 --> 02:03:57,560
and oftentimes arrive in their packaging

3014
02:03:57,560 --> 02:04:00,080
with eye protectors that
are actually designed

3015
02:04:00,080 --> 02:04:01,800
to shield out all the red light.

3016
02:04:01,800 --> 02:04:06,260
So take the potential dangers
of excessive illumination

3017
02:04:06,260 --> 02:04:09,290
of the eyes with any
wavelength of light seriously.

3018
02:04:09,290 --> 02:04:12,850
But if you're going to explore
670 and 790 nanometer light

3019
02:04:12,850 --> 02:04:16,380
for sake of enhancing neuronal function,

3020
02:04:16,380 --> 02:04:18,690
set it at a distance that's
comfortable to look at,

3021
02:04:18,690 --> 02:04:20,380
and that doesn't force you to squint

3022
02:04:20,380 --> 02:04:22,980
or doesn't make you feel
uncomfortable physically,

3023
02:04:22,980 --> 02:04:24,350
as if you need to turn away

3024
02:04:25,510 --> 02:04:26,343
during the period

3025
02:04:26,343 --> 02:04:28,810
of that two to three-minute
illumination each day.

3026
02:04:30,250 --> 02:04:32,430
In terms of turning away from light,

3027
02:04:32,430 --> 02:04:36,040
I'll just briefly mention
that that is not an accident

3028
02:04:36,040 --> 02:04:37,810
or a coincidence that
you have that response

3029
02:04:37,810 --> 02:04:39,030
to very bright light.

3030
02:04:39,030 --> 02:04:42,030
There is a so-called
photic avoidance pathway

3031
02:04:42,030 --> 02:04:43,680
that involves cells within your retina,

3032
02:04:43,680 --> 02:04:45,290
these ganglion cells that communicate

3033
02:04:45,290 --> 02:04:48,150
with yet another brain station,

3034
02:04:48,150 --> 02:04:50,980
a certain area of your
thalamus that communicate

3035
02:04:50,980 --> 02:04:53,610
to areas of your brain that
are associated with pain.

3036
02:04:53,610 --> 02:04:55,380
So literally that can trigger headache,

3037
02:04:55,380 --> 02:04:57,503
and that can trigger the squint reflex.

3038
02:04:58,420 --> 02:05:00,470
Biology is just beautiful in this way.

3039
02:05:00,470 --> 02:05:03,520
Too much light is bad for us
in that it can damage our eyes

3040
02:05:03,520 --> 02:05:05,190
and other aspects of our body.

3041
02:05:05,190 --> 02:05:07,430
So if we look at a
light that's too bright,

3042
02:05:07,430 --> 02:05:09,020
our eyes send a signal to the brain

3043
02:05:09,020 --> 02:05:10,410
that gives us a sort of a headache

3044
02:05:10,410 --> 02:05:12,140
and a desire to squint and turn away.

3045
02:05:12,140 --> 02:05:14,080
So that can be a useful guide

3046
02:05:14,080 --> 02:05:16,740
in terms of gauging how
bright a light should be

3047
02:05:16,740 --> 02:05:20,020
or at least how far away you
should be from a bright source

3048
02:05:20,020 --> 02:05:23,140
in order to safely engage
with that light source.

3049
02:05:23,140 --> 02:05:25,920
So the studies I just
described, once again,

3050
02:05:25,920 --> 02:05:28,020
involve the use of red
light early in the day

3051
02:05:28,020 --> 02:05:29,430
within three hours of waking

3052
02:05:29,430 --> 02:05:31,800
and are for the sake of
improving neuronal function.

3053
02:05:31,800 --> 02:05:35,810
Red light has also been
shown to be beneficial

3054
02:05:35,810 --> 02:05:38,200
late in the day and even
in the middle of the night.

3055
02:05:38,200 --> 02:05:40,300
And when I say middle of the night,

3056
02:05:40,300 --> 02:05:43,130
I'm referring to studies that
explore the use of red light

3057
02:05:43,130 --> 02:05:44,640
for shift workers.

3058
02:05:44,640 --> 02:05:46,420
I know that most people are not working

3059
02:05:46,420 --> 02:05:48,070
in the middle of the night,
at least I hope they're not,

3060
02:05:48,070 --> 02:05:50,470
but some of you may do
that from time to time.

3061
02:05:50,470 --> 02:05:51,480
All-nighters for studying,

3062
02:05:51,480 --> 02:05:53,610
I confess I still pull
all-nighters every once in a while

3063
02:05:53,610 --> 02:05:56,600
to prepare things like
podcasts and other deadlines.

3064
02:05:56,600 --> 02:05:59,780
I really try not to, happens
less and less as I get older,

3065
02:05:59,780 --> 02:06:01,590
because I think I get more disciplined

3066
02:06:01,590 --> 02:06:05,010
and/or less good at pulling all-nighters.

3067
02:06:05,010 --> 02:06:07,380
But I realize that many
people are doing shift work,

3068
02:06:07,380 --> 02:06:09,790
or they have to work
certainly past 10:00 pm.

3069
02:06:09,790 --> 02:06:11,650
Or maybe they're taking
care of young children

3070
02:06:11,650 --> 02:06:14,090
in the middle of the night,
and they have to be up.

3071
02:06:14,090 --> 02:06:16,450
In that case, red light can
actually be very beneficial.

3072
02:06:16,450 --> 02:06:19,050
And nowadays there are a
lot of sources of red light

3073
02:06:19,050 --> 02:06:20,880
available just as red light bulbs.

3074
02:06:20,880 --> 02:06:21,970
You don't need a panel.

3075
02:06:21,970 --> 02:06:25,260
So what I'm basically saying
is that it can be beneficial

3076
02:06:25,260 --> 02:06:28,140
to use red lights at night.

3077
02:06:28,140 --> 02:06:30,830
The study I'd like to emphasize
in this context is entitled,

3078
02:06:30,830 --> 02:06:34,210
Red Light: A Novel
Non-pharmacological Intervention

3079
02:06:34,210 --> 02:06:36,723
to Promote Alertness in Shift Workers.

3080
02:06:36,723 --> 02:06:38,040
It's a beautiful study.

3081
02:06:38,040 --> 02:06:41,400
They explored the use of
different wavelengths of light,

3082
02:06:41,400 --> 02:06:43,930
so blue light of 460 nanometers

3083
02:06:43,930 --> 02:06:46,740
or red light or dim white light,

3084
02:06:46,740 --> 02:06:49,540
of different brightnesses, et cetera,

3085
02:06:49,540 --> 02:06:52,740
and looked at things like melatonin.

3086
02:06:52,740 --> 02:06:55,190
How much does light of a given color

3087
02:06:55,190 --> 02:06:56,850
and intensity suppress melatonin?

3088
02:06:56,850 --> 02:06:58,620
They looked at cortisol, a stress hormone.

3089
02:06:58,620 --> 02:07:00,370
They looked at wakefulness,

3090
02:07:00,370 --> 02:07:03,640
how much or to what degree
could a given color of light

3091
02:07:03,640 --> 02:07:06,250
increase wakefulness at
different hours of the day?

3092
02:07:06,250 --> 02:07:08,340
The takeaway from this
study is very clear.

3093
02:07:08,340 --> 02:07:11,393
If you need to be awake late
at night for sake of shift work

3094
02:07:11,393 --> 02:07:14,810
or studying or taking care
of children, et cetera,

3095
02:07:14,810 --> 02:07:17,540
red light is going to be your best choice

3096
02:07:17,540 --> 02:07:21,253
because if the red light
is sufficiently dim,

3097
02:07:22,150 --> 02:07:25,040
it's not going to inhibit
melatonin production,

3098
02:07:25,040 --> 02:07:28,110
and it's not going to
increase cortisol at night.

3099
02:07:28,110 --> 02:07:30,840
Cortisol should be high early in the day,

3100
02:07:30,840 --> 02:07:32,390
or at least should be elevated relative

3101
02:07:32,390 --> 02:07:34,520
to other times of day if you are healthy.

3102
02:07:34,520 --> 02:07:36,870
A late shifted increase
in cortisol, however,

3103
02:07:36,870 --> 02:07:39,060
9:00 pm cortisol, 10:00 pm cortisol,

3104
02:07:39,060 --> 02:07:42,150
is well known to be
associated with depression

3105
02:07:42,150 --> 02:07:44,360
and other aspects of mental health,

3106
02:07:44,360 --> 02:07:46,400
or I should say mental illness.

3107
02:07:46,400 --> 02:07:50,140
So if you do need to be awake
at night or even all night,

3108
02:07:50,140 --> 02:07:53,660
red light is going to be
the preferred light source.

3109
02:07:53,660 --> 02:07:55,410
And in terms of how bright to make it,

3110
02:07:55,410 --> 02:07:58,180
well, as dim as you can,

3111
02:07:58,180 --> 02:08:00,090
while still being able
to perform the activities

3112
02:08:00,090 --> 02:08:00,923
that you need to perform.

3113
02:08:00,923 --> 02:08:03,090
That's going to be your best guide.

3114
02:08:03,090 --> 02:08:05,460
I'll provide a link to this study as well.

3115
02:08:05,460 --> 02:08:08,150
Again, it's a really important study

3116
02:08:08,150 --> 02:08:10,360
because it emphasized that
there are forms of light,

3117
02:08:10,360 --> 02:08:12,280
red light, provided it's dim,

3118
02:08:12,280 --> 02:08:15,420
that can allow you to
stimulate the alertness

3119
02:08:15,420 --> 02:08:19,130
that light landing on
the eyes can provide.

3120
02:08:19,130 --> 02:08:20,230
So it allows you to stay awake

3121
02:08:20,230 --> 02:08:22,550
and to do whatever work
that you need to do.

3122
02:08:22,550 --> 02:08:26,070
It does not seem to alter
melatonin production,

3123
02:08:26,070 --> 02:08:26,903
so that's good.

3124
02:08:26,903 --> 02:08:28,920
It does not seem to alter levels

3125
02:08:28,920 --> 02:08:31,040
or timing of cortisol production.

3126
02:08:31,040 --> 02:08:34,720
So yet another case where
red light used correctly

3127
02:08:34,720 --> 02:08:35,830
can be beneficial.

3128
02:08:35,830 --> 02:08:37,040
Up until now, we've been talking

3129
02:08:37,040 --> 02:08:39,785
about the effects of shining
different wavelengths of light

3130
02:08:39,785 --> 02:08:43,160
on the skin or on our eyes

3131
02:08:43,160 --> 02:08:47,610
and the downstream health
consequences of that illumination.

3132
02:08:47,610 --> 02:08:49,600
However, one of the most important goals

3133
02:08:49,600 --> 02:08:52,050
of science and medicine is to figure out

3134
02:08:52,050 --> 02:08:54,620
how to change the health of our brain.

3135
02:08:54,620 --> 02:08:58,280
And of course, our brain is
contained within our skull,

3136
02:08:58,280 --> 02:09:01,210
and therefore we can't just shine light

3137
02:09:01,210 --> 02:09:03,490
onto the outside of our head

3138
02:09:03,490 --> 02:09:05,410
and expect it to change the activity

3139
02:09:05,410 --> 02:09:07,030
of neurons deep within the brain,

3140
02:09:07,030 --> 02:09:11,590
unless those neurons are
linked up with our eyes

3141
02:09:11,590 --> 02:09:12,620
or with our skin.

3142
02:09:12,620 --> 02:09:14,430
And as it turns out, even
though there are a lot

3143
02:09:14,430 --> 02:09:17,710
of brain areas that are
connected through neural circuits

3144
02:09:17,710 --> 02:09:19,610
and hormone circuits through our eye,

3145
02:09:19,610 --> 02:09:22,280
and believe it or not, also to our skin,

3146
02:09:22,280 --> 02:09:24,163
many brain areas are not.

3147
02:09:25,860 --> 02:09:27,830
Brain areas such as the hippocampus,

3148
02:09:27,830 --> 02:09:30,280
which is involved in learning and memory,

3149
02:09:30,280 --> 02:09:33,220
brain areas such as our neocortex,

3150
02:09:33,220 --> 02:09:36,510
well, some areas of our neocortex
such as our visual cortex

3151
02:09:36,510 --> 02:09:38,410
are indirectly linked to our eyes,

3152
02:09:38,410 --> 02:09:39,660
so if we shine light in our eyes,

3153
02:09:39,660 --> 02:09:42,450
we can change the activity
of neurons in our neocortex,

3154
02:09:42,450 --> 02:09:44,970
but there are other brain areas

3155
02:09:44,970 --> 02:09:48,860
that are not directly or
even indirectly connected

3156
02:09:48,860 --> 02:09:50,100
to our visual system,

3157
02:09:50,100 --> 02:09:53,140
not at least in any immediate way.

3158
02:09:53,140 --> 02:09:54,140
So that raises the question

3159
02:09:54,140 --> 02:09:56,450
of how do you change the
activity of neurons in the brain?

3160
02:09:56,450 --> 02:09:58,140
Well, there's pharmacology.

3161
02:09:58,140 --> 02:10:01,100
You can take pills, you can inject drugs

3162
02:10:01,100 --> 02:10:02,657
that will change the
pharmacology of neurons

3163
02:10:02,657 --> 02:10:04,860
and the way they operate and fire.

3164
02:10:04,860 --> 02:10:07,810
Of course, antidepressants
are one such instance,

3165
02:10:07,810 --> 02:10:09,750
opioid drugs are another.

3166
02:10:09,750 --> 02:10:12,740
There's a huge array of
psychoactive compounds,

3167
02:10:12,740 --> 02:10:14,730
meaning compounds that
will change the levels

3168
02:10:14,730 --> 02:10:16,800
of chemicals in your brain.

3169
02:10:16,800 --> 02:10:17,680
Some of those work,

3170
02:10:17,680 --> 02:10:20,730
many of them also carry side effects.

3171
02:10:20,730 --> 02:10:22,580
It's all rather indirect,

3172
02:10:22,580 --> 02:10:24,360
meaning you have lots of different cells

3173
02:10:24,360 --> 02:10:25,340
in different areas of your brain

3174
02:10:25,340 --> 02:10:26,670
that utilize the same chemicals.

3175
02:10:26,670 --> 02:10:29,100
So a drug, for instance,
to increase serotonin

3176
02:10:29,100 --> 02:10:31,540
for sake of improving depression

3177
02:10:31,540 --> 02:10:33,590
will also often have the effect

3178
02:10:33,590 --> 02:10:37,020
of reducing certain neurons

3179
02:10:37,020 --> 02:10:39,010
output of serotonin in the hippocampus

3180
02:10:39,010 --> 02:10:41,300
and cause changes in
appetite or changes in libido

3181
02:10:41,300 --> 02:10:42,453
and so on and so forth.

3182
02:10:43,490 --> 02:10:45,290
You could imagine using
electrical stimulation,

3183
02:10:45,290 --> 02:10:46,480
putting wires into the brain

3184
02:10:46,480 --> 02:10:48,550
and stimulating specific brain areas

3185
02:10:48,550 --> 02:10:51,360
in order to activate the
neurons in those brain areas.

3186
02:10:51,360 --> 02:10:54,010
And certainly that works and
has been done experimentally

3187
02:10:54,010 --> 02:10:56,900
and is done during
neurosurgery exams, et cetera,

3188
02:10:56,900 --> 02:10:59,650
but involves removing a piece of skull.

3189
02:10:59,650 --> 02:11:01,340
So that's not very practical.

3190
02:11:01,340 --> 02:11:04,390
In principle, light
would be a wonderful way

3191
02:11:04,390 --> 02:11:08,510
to modulate the activity of
neurons deep within the brain.

3192
02:11:08,510 --> 02:11:10,363
But again, the skull is in the way.

3193
02:11:11,560 --> 02:11:14,430
Recent studies, however,
have figured out ways

3194
02:11:14,430 --> 02:11:16,730
that light can be delivered to the eyes

3195
02:11:16,730 --> 02:11:20,250
to change global patterns
of firing in the brain

3196
02:11:20,250 --> 02:11:22,690
in ways that can be
beneficial to the brain.

3197
02:11:22,690 --> 02:11:25,530
And the work that I'm referring to now

3198
02:11:25,530 --> 02:11:28,600
is mainly the work of Li-Huei Tsai at MIT,

3199
02:11:28,600 --> 02:11:32,210
Massachusetts Institute of
Technology, and her colleagues.

3200
02:11:32,210 --> 02:11:34,880
And what they've discovered
that there's a particular

3201
02:11:34,880 --> 02:11:38,970
pattern of brain activity
called gamma activity.

3202
02:11:38,970 --> 02:11:42,100
Gamma activity is one so-called wavelength

3203
02:11:42,100 --> 02:11:44,240
of electrical activity in the brain,

3204
02:11:44,240 --> 02:11:45,270
so not wavelengths of light,

3205
02:11:45,270 --> 02:11:48,010
but wavelengths of electrical
activity in the brain

3206
02:11:48,010 --> 02:11:50,550
that can be restorative
for certain aspects

3207
02:11:50,550 --> 02:11:51,600
of learning and memory

3208
02:11:51,600 --> 02:11:55,210
and can actually help create
molecular changes in neurons

3209
02:11:55,210 --> 02:11:57,650
that lead to clearance of debris

3210
02:11:57,650 --> 02:12:01,800
and even reductions in
age-related cognitive decline.

3211
02:12:01,800 --> 02:12:06,800
So the way to think about brain
waves and brain oscillations

3212
02:12:06,970 --> 02:12:09,320
is that neurons are electrically active,

3213
02:12:09,320 --> 02:12:11,150
that involves chemicals, et cetera.

3214
02:12:11,150 --> 02:12:14,877
And they can be active in
very slow, big waveforms.

3215
02:12:14,877 --> 02:12:18,310
So you can think of, you
know, Delta waves, meaning,

3216
02:12:18,310 --> 02:12:20,430
so you can imagine a wave
of electrical activity

3217
02:12:20,430 --> 02:12:22,240
that comes along very infrequently.

3218
02:12:22,240 --> 02:12:24,280
So a given neuron fires,

3219
02:12:24,280 --> 02:12:26,970
and then some period of time later fires,

3220
02:12:26,970 --> 02:12:29,730
and then some period of
time even later fires.

3221
02:12:29,730 --> 02:12:32,550
Or you can imagine that that
same cell is very active,

3222
02:12:32,550 --> 02:12:34,390
fires, fires, fires, fires, fires.

3223
02:12:34,390 --> 02:12:36,050
You can imagine if it's firing very often,

3224
02:12:36,050 --> 02:12:38,450
it's going to be short wavelength, right?

3225
02:12:38,450 --> 02:12:40,380
Shorter gaps between firing.

3226
02:12:40,380 --> 02:12:43,600
Or if it's firing very seldom,

3227
02:12:43,600 --> 02:12:45,510
you're going to think about that

3228
02:12:45,510 --> 02:12:47,310
as longer wavelength firing.

3229
02:12:47,310 --> 02:12:51,070
Turns out that gamma waves
are one pattern of firing

3230
02:12:51,070 --> 02:12:54,810
that lead to downstream
metabolic functions

3231
02:12:54,810 --> 02:12:57,380
and biological functions that
end up clearing away debris

3232
02:12:57,380 --> 02:13:00,250
that's associated with aging in cells

3233
02:13:00,250 --> 02:13:03,340
and that also lead to molecular changes

3234
02:13:03,340 --> 02:13:06,430
that enhance the kind of
youthfulness of neurons,

3235
02:13:06,430 --> 02:13:07,263
so to speak.

3236
02:13:09,230 --> 02:13:12,450
How do we induce gamma
oscillations within the brain?

3237
02:13:12,450 --> 02:13:15,730
Well, what Li-Huei Tsai and colleagues

3238
02:13:15,730 --> 02:13:17,260
have beautifully shown

3239
02:13:17,260 --> 02:13:22,080
is that by delivering certain
patterns of light flicker,

3240
02:13:22,080 --> 02:13:25,350
so lights going on and off
at a particular frequency,

3241
02:13:25,350 --> 02:13:28,530
the brain as a whole starts to entrain,

3242
02:13:28,530 --> 02:13:30,900
meaning it matches to
those particular patterns

3243
02:13:30,900 --> 02:13:31,733
of light flicker,

3244
02:13:31,733 --> 02:13:34,400
even though many of the
brain areas that do this

3245
02:13:34,400 --> 02:13:38,710
are not directly within the
visual system or visual pathway.

3246
02:13:38,710 --> 02:13:42,090
So the studies that I'm
referring to are several,

3247
02:13:42,090 --> 02:13:43,950
but the one that I'd like
to highlight is entitled,

3248
02:13:43,950 --> 02:13:46,820
Gamma Entrainment Binds
Higher-Order Brain Regions

3249
02:13:46,820 --> 02:13:48,170
and Offers Neuroprotection.

3250
02:13:49,318 --> 02:13:50,670
What they essentially did

3251
02:13:50,670 --> 02:13:54,870
was to expose subjects to 40 hertz,

3252
02:13:54,870 --> 02:13:58,120
which is a particular
frequency of illumination,

3253
02:13:58,120 --> 02:13:59,170
to the eyes.

3254
02:13:59,170 --> 02:14:01,360
So it's light goes on, light goes off,

3255
02:14:01,360 --> 02:14:06,250
light goes on, light goes off
at a frequency of 40 hertz.

3256
02:14:06,250 --> 02:14:09,310
And when they did that and
they recorded the activity

3257
02:14:09,310 --> 02:14:10,410
of neurons within the brain,

3258
02:14:10,410 --> 02:14:12,960
not just within the
visual areas of the brain,

3259
02:14:12,960 --> 02:14:14,870
but within other areas as well,

3260
02:14:14,870 --> 02:14:18,860
they observed increased
gamma oscillations,

3261
02:14:18,860 --> 02:14:23,070
meaning that the electrical
activity of the brain at large

3262
02:14:23,070 --> 02:14:26,110
started to match to the patterns of light

3263
02:14:26,110 --> 02:14:28,020
that were delivered to the eyes.

3264
02:14:28,020 --> 02:14:29,770
This is really exciting and very unique

3265
02:14:29,770 --> 02:14:31,720
from the different types of phototherapies

3266
02:14:31,720 --> 02:14:33,220
that we've been talking
about up until now.

3267
02:14:33,220 --> 02:14:35,210
All the patterns of phototherapy

3268
02:14:35,210 --> 02:14:36,730
that we've been talking about up until now

3269
02:14:36,730 --> 02:14:39,340
involved constant illumination
with a given wavelength.

3270
02:14:39,340 --> 02:14:44,340
Here, it is wavelength generating
patterns of illumination,

3271
02:14:44,930 --> 02:14:46,620
light on, light off, light on, light off,

3272
02:14:46,620 --> 02:14:48,530
at a particular frequency.

3273
02:14:48,530 --> 02:14:49,780
So what they found, for instance,

3274
02:14:49,780 --> 02:14:51,250
using this pattern of stimulation,

3275
02:14:51,250 --> 02:14:53,690
and by the way, the
stimulation was called genus,

3276
02:14:53,690 --> 02:14:56,180
gamma entrainment using
sensory stimulation,

3277
02:14:56,180 --> 02:14:57,320
so G-E-N-U-S,

3278
02:14:57,320 --> 02:15:00,030
gamma entrainment using
sensory stimulation,

3279
02:15:00,030 --> 02:15:01,610
had a number of really
interesting effects.

3280
02:15:01,610 --> 02:15:04,950
First of all, it reduced
so-called amyloid plaques

3281
02:15:04,950 --> 02:15:06,710
and phosphorylated tau.

3282
02:15:06,710 --> 02:15:08,400
Amyloid plaques and phosphorylated tau

3283
02:15:08,400 --> 02:15:09,810
are associated with Alzheimer's

3284
02:15:09,810 --> 02:15:12,890
and normal age related cognitive decline.

